23/02/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The presiding judge in the trial of Slobodan Milosevic has resigned, the international war crimes tribunal announced on Sunday (22 February).
Judge Richard May will step down on 31 May because of a recently discovered illness.
Theodor Meron, the president of the tribunal, said in a statement that he was confident May's resignation would not affect the trial.
He expressed confidence that UN Secretary General Kofi Annan would soon appoint a successor.
(BBC - 23/02/04;
Reuters, AFP - 22/02/04)
